ls a “street theology.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHip-hopzUnited StatesxReligious aspects. 0aPopular musiczLatin AmericaxHistory and criticism. 0aRap (Music)xHistory and criticism. 0aRap (Music)xReligious aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  arap, hip-hop, reggaeton, street theology, liberation theology, fragments, religion, mysticism, aesthetics, prophecy.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226819150423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226819150/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles